newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds see light trade on weaker dollar.
newsitem.headline: European feeds see light trade on weaker dollar.

text.p: The European meals and feeds market saw a few trades at lower levels as buyers covered nearby positions on the back of a weaker dollar, market sources said.

"It was not much and a lower Chicago soymeal futures opening also did not help spark activity ahead of the weekend. Therefore business was confined to nearby material as sellers eased their asking prices," one broker said.

Arrived Brazilian soymeal traded at $309 a tonne cif Rotterdam and May at $307 cif. May and June Dutch high protein soymeal both traded at $327 fob Rotterdam. May Argentine sunmeal pellets traded at $135 and June at $134 cif Rotterdam.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
